Text.Value: It's a view I would once have shared with my companion. Though definitely unaccompanied by such revelry.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wistful, missing an old friend

Text.Value: Don't stop now. What else do you like about me?
You remind me of her somewhat. An expression you both share - when she gives in to her more feline qualities, a mouse trapped beneath her paw...
Not that I don't appreciate your musk. I actually rather like it...

EditorData.NodeContext: Getting carried away, accidentally revealed he's kind of interested in the player romantically

Text.Value: A beautiful night, don't you think? Nothing like a brush with destruction to make one appreciate the majesty of the celestial canvas.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wistful, missing an old friend

Text.Value: Nonetheless, your finer qualities are remarkably plentiful.
Right. Understood. You shall hear no more on the subject from me.
I used to while away many hours just like these with my companion, though in far comfier surrounds.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wistful, missing an old friend

Text.Value: Don't worry about me - I'm quite content to enjoy the party from here. Go, enjoy yourself.
Suffice it to say, I think rather a lot of you. And there aren't many on this plane who I'd give such high praise.
Friends with the mighty Gale of Waterdeep? I'd be honoured.
Actually, I was thinking we'd be wonderful together...
Who are you referring to? A former lover, perhaps?
I assure you, were you to meet Tara you would see the comparison for the flattery it is. But perhaps that's not a point worth labouring further.
I'm flattered. Is your good opinion so hard to come by?
Please - feel free to enjoy yourself elsewhere. No doubt there are others here who offer more welcome company.
I've got aquaintances, certainly. Plenty of colleagues. But friends? Those are precious indeed.
'Smart' does her a disservice. She's a fine wizard in her own right, though somewhat held back by her lack of opposable thumbs.
After so long being cared for by someone else, it feels good to have repaid the favour. Not directly to Tara, but to these poor tieflings. I'm sure she would approve.
What is Tara like?
Don't stop there. What else do you like about me?
The pleasures I experienced in Mystra's embrace go far beyond the thrill of having one's tummy tickled. I remember once, she took the smallest piece of the Weave and made it into -

EditorData.NodeContext: Taking the question seriously, missing the flirtatious side of it

Text.Value: She'll love you. So long as you don't rub her belly. She hates it when anyone does that.
I'm glad. To know you enjoy my company is, well, it's rather wonderful actually. I'd be loathe to waste the time of someone who's become rather important to me.
I see. Then perhaps we see each other in the same light after all. A resplendent one, flush with warmth and anticipation, but one which I must shy away from, for now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Still flustered, but pleased to learn you like him romantically. Then getting to the point - he can't do anything until the orb is dealt with

Text.Value: I'd given up on myself, but Tara never did. It was her encouragement, her research that led me to my treatment. Once we knew that magically-infused items were the key, she went out to find them for me. She saved my life.
Go, indulge in the frivolities - they're good for the heart. And mine will be all the lighter, to see you enjoying yourself.
She sounds like a fine animal. One I'd be honoured to know.
Even in such fraught times as these, there is peace to be found in the stillness as evening draws in.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wistful, missing an old friend

Text.Value: Wine is to wit as meat is to... to... oh, I can't bloody remember it. There I go, then, proving your point.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to sound impressive, a bit flustered

Text.Value: What if she doesn't like me?
I wouldn't call this a friendship. More a series of necessary interactions.
I wish she were here for me to make a formal introduction, but I would never ask her to undertake such a journey. She is safer at home.
I assure you, when I tell someone they're wonderful - I mean it. And you are wonderful.

EditorData.NodeContext: sincere, giving way the depth of his growing feelings fro the player

Text.Value: Go - enjoy your evening. Nothing better for the heart than a good night's rest, and mine is gladdened to know I'll have the pleasure of your company again come morning.
You remind me of her somewhat. There's a steeliness to you, an unwavering tenacity even in the face of, to be frank, quite dire odds.
Tara is not any cat. She's a tressym. And given your confusion, I'm guessing you've never met one. They're brilliant creatures - fine company for any self-respecting wizard.
Besides, she was always telling me I needed to spread my wings, so to speak. Find mortal friends, instead of hanging onto Mystra's coattails. So that's what I'm doing. I hope.
I hope you aren't talking about Mystra again...
One doesn't become the most powerful archmage in Waterdeep and lover to the goddess of magic herself by having low standards.
You remind me of her somewhat. The same sharp tongue. And sharp teeth.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not too heavy on the 'sharp teeth' - I'm not sure it's guaranteed that Gale knows Astarion is a vampire.

Text.Value: I speak of Tara, my tressym, assistant, my constant companion through all the ills and tribulations my hubris has thrust upon me.

You're the first person I've spent any significant time with in a year or more. Spending time in your company, I realise that I may have left behind the greater part of my wit, and sensitivity, in my tower.
You remind me of her somewhat. Something in the way you roll your eyes when I speak...
Do you like having your belly rubbed?
Sadly not. If I'm being entirely honest, my social circle is rather small. More of a dot. Or a pinhead.
You must have been lonely, with only Tara for company...
Bad luck on that front - I'm actually a nymph in disguise...
Then let me say it more plainly -
However, my sentiments are all I can offer at present. With my condition as volatile as it is, I wouldn't want to indulge in any undue, erm, excitement. So to speak.

EditorData.NodeContext: Telling the player he can't progress their romance further until he has cured the orb

Text.Value: You know what, I think I've clearly had far too much wine. And you've had nowhere near enough. I think this is a conversation best held back on - for now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Flustered, hesitating to explicitly say what he thinks you were offering, then backtracking altogether

Text.Value: I think you're rather wonderful. And that's not a word I waste on anyone unworthy of it.
She preferred it when we were alone, curled up before a crackling hearth with some ancient, esoteric tome between us, ink glinting in the firelight...

EditorData.NodeContext: Recalling a rich, warming memory

Text.Value: Being mentioned in the same breath as your pet isn't the compliment you think it is...
She has a good heart, and she would recognise the same in your actions here. I'm sure she'd approve of me lending myself to your efforts.
Sometimes. But I imposed it upon myself, after all. I set up enough wards to keep an army at bay, never mind the few colleagues who sought to inquire about my welfare.
Tara did her best to keep my spirits up, of course, but there's only so much one tressym can make up for one's entire social circle. And she was often gone seeking items to treat my condition.
I can't say I share the same high opinion of you, Gale.
She'd be proud to see me keeping such fine company - the saviour of those poor tieflings, no less. And I've given her precious little to be proud of recently.
You don't have any friends?
Not an animal lover? Nobody's perfect, I suppose.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sincere - he's offering something that has meaning, a sign of how much he likes you

Text.Value: If this is an attempt at flirting, you should stop. I'm not interested.
She sounds great. But I was hoping I meant more to you than an animal companion...
Consider this budding romance thoroughly nipped. Though I hope our friendship need not come to such an abrupt end.
That depends. What do you like about me?

EditorData.logicalname: Finished spell teaching, didn't picture romance

Text.Value: Don't let me drag you away. Enjoy yourself - you earned a night of revelry.
I rather like the Gale stood in front of me. In fact, I'd like to see more of him...
Of course. I hoped we might be more than friends...
I'm not interested in you, Gale. Not in that way.
Always bringing such candour to our conversations. Some would think twice about mocking Gale of Waterdeep, but you just go straight for the gut.

EditorData.NodeContext: Playing along, making fun of himself

Text.Value: The feeling's mutual - you're a wonderful friend. Though usually more... erudite.
Are you... are you talking about your cat?
No one came to visit you during your confinement?
Wait. Are you saying...

EditorData.NodeContext: Realising that the player was flirting, getting flustered

Text.Value: She must be very smart, to have done all that.
I like that about you. It's one of your rarer qualities, though I fear my ego can take no more of it tonight.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cheerfully accepting the brush off, not taking it personally

Text.Value: You're doing just fine, Gale.
After I was afflicted with my condition, I locked myself in my tower for an entire year. I was inconsolable, wallowing in my self-inflicted tragedy.
So I remind you of your pet? How romantic...
With my condition as volatile as it is, I fear any undue, er, excitement, may tip it over the edge. So to speak.
Not as much as I hate talking about cats. Is there nothing else on your mind?
Perhaps we'd better leave it at that. My ineloquent tongue isn't worthy of your ear at present.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cheerfully accepting the brush off, not taking it personally

Text.Value: You remind me of her somewhat. You share her fierceness, and her passion.
You remind me of her somewhat. You share her pragmatic streak.
Well, this seems as good a time as any for me to stop babbling on.

EditorData.NodeContext: being awkward

Text.Value: Sounds, er, fun.
Not everyone is comfortable being alone with their thoughts. Though I never felt alone with a book in my hand. Or with her for company.

EditorData.NodeContext: Being generous towards the player's lack of interest, then returning to his reflective mood

Text.Value: Were I to recite that list, I fear we'd still be here at dusk tomorrow. Many things, I assure you, but a conversation better saved for another time.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cheerfully deflecting your question, though it's clear he would have more to say

Text.Value: Very funny. But as we all know, nymphs are sticklers when it comes to their bathing routines. You, my friend, haven't been near a fresh spring in a tenday or more.

EditorData.NodeContext: Good humoured ribbing

Text.Value: You remind me of her somewhat. You share a certain nobility of spirit.
She'd be most impressed by our efforts saving these tieflings. Proud, even. And I've given her little to be proud of recently.
By Ahghairon's lost nose - no!

EditorData.NodeContext: Shocked at the player's suggestion. Note: this is a statue in Waterdeep's religious burial district

Text.Value: I hope, though we've only known each other for a short time, I might be able to count you among that number?

Synopsis: After the party, this companion is still trying to come down from all the energy, and with a good enough bond it is possible for the player avatar to flirt and unlock a romance option. Gale has been drinking wine, but is not drunk - line delivery shouldn't convey this unless expressly indicated in the VO notes. The wine is mentioned in a few spots, but it shouldn't influence his diction.
